        <title>Manifold Absolute Pressure (MAP) Sensor</title>
        <figure id="f2651014" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ09/J09015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="240px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 366. MAP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The MAP sensor, a ceramic diaphragm sensor, detects intake manifold boost pressure.</para>
        <para>The MAP signal is monitored by the ECM for EGR position and engine fueling calculations.</para>
        <para>The MAP sensor is installed in the top front of the intake manifold.</para>
